üß† What is React?
React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces (UIs), especially for single-page applications (SPAs).

üèóÔ∏è Created by Facebook in 2013, React helps developers build fast, interactive websites using components and a virtual DOM.

| Traditional JS/HTML/CSS               | React                                        |
| ------------------------------------  | -------------------------------------------  |
| -Manually updates the DOM             | -React automatically updates the DOM         |
| -Messy code for dynamic UIs           | -Uses clean reusable components              |
| -Hard to manage large apps            | -Easy to scale with components and state     |
| -Performance issues with many updates | -Uses **Virtual DOM** for better performance |
